Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely chop @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%oz}; chop into bite-size pieces if necessary. Peel and thinly slice @garlic{2%cloves}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 3/4 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz} and onion; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until sausage is mostly cooked through and onion is softened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in kale and garlic; cook until sausage is cooked through and kale is wilted, ~{3-5%minutes}. TIP: Add kale in batches if necessary.

Reduce heat to medium. Stir in @cream sauce base{4%oz}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water, and a big squeeze of lemon juice. Cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Reduce heat to low. Stir in drained cavatappi, half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}(grated) (use the rest for serving), @butter{2%tbsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice. TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between bowls; top with remaining Parmesan. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.